WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified body profile for the Sony VENICE 2 camera. It contains the
exact mathematical IDT (Input Device Transform), S-Log3 curve parameters
with their inverse, native color space primaries, white balance presets,
dual base ISO specifications, and sensor metrology data. This is the
single source of truth for linearizing VENICE 2 footage to scene-referred
ACES2065-1.

WHY IT EXISTS
Sony’s Cinema Line uses S-Gamut3.Cine and S-Log3 to encode up to 15.3
stops of dynamic range. Integrating VENICE 2 footage into an ACES or GIOP
pipeline demands an exact, verified inverse transform. This file replaces
the need for proprietary Sony LUTs or the Catalyst SDK, providing an
open, auditable mathematical path back to linear scene light.

HOW IT WORKS
The file defines the transform chain:
  1. Inverse S‑Log3 (piecewise, with the linear toe) → linear
     S‑Gamut3.Cine RGB.
  2. S‑Gamut3.Cine to ACES2065‑1 matrix (3×3, D65‑to‑D60 adaptation).
  3. White balance gain inverse (as‑shot or preset).
  4. Dual Base ISO metadata: the IDT itself is ISO‑agnostic, but the
     correct analog gain state (low 800 / high 3200) is documented.
All constants are certified for the 8.6K and 6K VENICE 2 variants.

